 in favour of the Electric Group, and has given The Leadmill Ltd about three months and 21 days to leave the site (via <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/crlx83xk77jo" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>BBC</em></a> ). Bosses of the Leadmill have shared that they will be exhausting “every possible legal avenue to secure our future, retain our staff and protect our venue,” (via <a href="https://www.thestar.co.uk/business/consumer/the-leadmill-sheffield-club-bosses-given-deadline-to-leave-following-court-defeat-4999668" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Star</em></a> ). </p><figure id="attachment_3840263" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3840263" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3840263" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Graham-Coxon-performing.jpg" alt="Graham Coxon performing at the Leadmill in Sheffield (Photo by Gary Wolstenholme/Redferns)" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Graham-Coxon-performing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Graham-Coxon-performing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Graham-Coxon-performing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Graham-Coxon-performing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Graham-Coxon-performing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Graham-Coxon-performing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3840263" class="wp-caption-text"> Graham Coxon performing at the Leadmill in Sheffield (Photo by Gary Wolstenholme/Redferns)</figcaption></figure><p> A spokesperson for the Electric Group <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/new-leadmill-landlords-promise-bright-future-for-this-venue-as-a-cornerstone-of-the-live-music-scene-in-sheffield-for-the-next-100-years-after-winning-court-ruling-3839728">previously commented on the ruling to <em>NME</em></a> : “We welcome the court&#39;s consideration and careful decision to award a possession order for the Leadmill; an important ruling following difficult legal proceedings.</p><p> “The successful legal outcome paves the way for a bright future for this venue, ensuring it will receive the substantial investment it needs to thrive. It will continue to be a cornerstone of the live music scene in Sheffield, supporting artists, fans, and community projects for the next 100 years.”</p><p> The update came days after The Leadmill&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sheffield-leadmill-lose-planning-application-to-gut-parts-of-the-venue-if-evicted-3838744">planning application to demolish certain parts of the venue, if evicted, was rejected</a> . The Leadmill&#39;s Phil Mills previously said he intended to “gut” the premises of its current fixtures and fittings – including the dancefloor and stage – if forced to vacate the building.</p><p> Since first opening its doors in 1980, the venue has hosted early shows from <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/arctic-monkeys">Arctic Monkeys</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kings-of-leon">Kings Of Leon</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-killers">The Killers</a> , and remains a popular live music and clubbing spot. </p><figure id="attachment_3840264" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3840264" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3840264" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Pulp-at-the-leadmill-plaque.jpg" alt="A general view of the Leadmill night club in Sheffield. City centre on 1 April 2022. (Photo by Giannis Alexopoulos/NurPhoto via Getty Images)" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Pulp-at-the-leadmill-plaque.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Pulp-at-the-leadmill-plaque-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Pulp-at-the-leadmill-plaque-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Pulp-at-the-leadmill-plaque-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Pulp-at-the-leadmill-plaque-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Pulp-at-the-leadmill-plaque-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3840264" class="wp-caption-text"> A general view of the Leadmill night club in Sheffield. City centre on 1 April 2022. (Photo by Giannis Alexopoulos/NurPhoto via Getty Images)</figcaption></figure><p> Though nothing has been confirmed, The Leadmill&#39;s Phil Mills said in December it <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-leadmill-in-sheffield-could-move-to-new-location-if-evicted-3823532">could possibly move to a new location if evicted, though that wouldn&#39;t be its primary option</a> despite owning the trademark rights to The Leadmill&#39;s name and branding: “If we found a suitable premises in Sheffield we would effectively be competing against ourselves because The Leadmill&#39;s name and legacy is indivisible in our customers&#39; minds,” he said.</p><p> After news of it coming under threat emerged in 2022, former <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jeremy-corbyn-joins-campaign-to-save-sheffield-leadmill-3227527">Labour leader Jeremy Corbyn visited The Leadmill and encouraged others to “get behind it</a> . He also echoed <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/leadmill-sheffield-eviction-closure-arctic-monkeys-tour-manager-local-reaction-3201505">the views of countless Sheffield locals</a> , hailing it as “the heart of the city”, as well as the stance held by <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/local-stars-rally-around-leadmill-as-new-owners-register-for-name-electric-sheffield-3197594">Arctic Monkeys, Jarvis Cocker and Bring Me The Horizon&#39;s Oli Sykes among the Sheffield artists to have spoken out in support of the venue</a> .</p><p> Sheffield&#39;s Richard Hawley has also been <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/local-stars-rally-around-leadmill-as-new-owners-register-for-name-electric-sheffield-3197594">a vocal supporter of The Leadmill</a> for years now – having played <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/richard-hawley-announces-fourth-and-final-show-to-help-support-sheffield-leadmill-3205041">a number of gigs there throughout 2022 to raise money and awareness</a> . Some of his shows also saw him <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jarvis-cocker-joins-richard-hawley-at-leadmill-show-urges-owners-have-some-respect-for-a-beautiful-thing-3286723">joined on stage by fellow Sheffield artists Jarvis Cocker</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-self-esteem-perform-with-richard-hawley-during-sheffield-leadmill-residency-3285971">Rebecca Taylor (aka Self Esteem)</a> . </p><figure id="attachment_3286984" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3286984" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3286984" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Richard-Hawley-Jarvis-Cocker-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3286984" class="wp-caption-text"> Richard Hawley and Jarvis Cocker onstage at the Leadmill in Sheffield on August 9, 2022. Credit: Tom Sunderland</figcaption></figure><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/richard-hawley-interview-standing-at-the-skys-edge-musical-pulp-arctic-monkeys-self-esteem-leadmill-3394667">Speaking to <em>NME</em></a> about the history behind the venue in February 2023, Hawley said that the staff who&#39;ve built up the venue over the years <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/richard-hawley-interview-standing-at-the-skys-edge-musical-pulp-arctic-monkeys-self-esteem-leadmill-3394667">should be allowed to continue running it under the same name</a> .</p><p> “The upsetting thing is that if it was a failing business, I&#39;d understand that someone would take it over. What angers me is that it doesn&#39;t surprise me that greedy fuckers buy the land from underneath them. If they threw [the venue staff] out and turned it into flats, it would be an absolute tragedy but slightly easier to accept,” he said.</p><p> “The fact that what they&#39;ve basically done is bought the land from underneath them, issued them with an eviction notice, and are going to steal their business. That to me is wildly immoral. If I was running a venue, or even a chip shop, I&#39;d think, &#39;Hold on a sec, if they get away with it with these, then who&#39;s next?&#39; It&#39;s just wrong.”</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sheffield-leadmill-given-date-to-move-out-of-venue-after-losing-court-battle-3840233">Sheffield Leadmill given date to move out of venue after losing court battle</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
